<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Mapping-out-agriculture-and-food-security-in-changing-climate" title="Mapping out agriculture and food security in changing climate" alt="link">Mapping out agriculture and food security in changing climate</a></h2>

	
					<p>The Joint Programming Initiative <a href="http://www.faccejpi.com/" target="_blank">FACCE–JPI</a> has announced the approval for funding of its first joint action which brings together 67 research groups from 17 European countries. The initiative’s research agenda will address the modelling of impacts of climate change on European agriculture and food security and the reduction of uncertainties in climate change scenarios. An innovative, tailor-made instrument, a ‘Knowledge Hub’, was developed by the FACCE–JPI, associating three complementary dimensions: networking, research and capacity building. (Via <a href="http://www.wur.nl/UK/newsagenda/news/N_Facce_.htm" target="_self">WUR</a>, 12/04/2012)</p>
							<p><span class="date">31/05/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
	<a class="link" href="/en/Dossiers/CTA-and-S-T/Developments/Mapping-out-agriculture-and-food-security-in-changing-climate">Read more...</a>
